"""
Drug Combinations Synergy Tool - Synergistic Drug Combination Discovery

ARCHITECTURE DECISION LOG:
v1.0 (current): Bliss independence model with embedding-based predictions
  - Computes pairwise synergy using Bliss independence deviation
  - Predicts synergy from drug embedding similarity
  - Uses antipodal rescue scores as effect measures
  - Returns commercial names for all drugs

Pattern: Follows vector_antipodal.py for rescue scoring
Reference: /Users/expo/Code/expo/clients/quiver/quiver_platform/zones/z07_data_access/tools/vector_antipodal.py

Bliss Independence Model:
  - synergy_score = observed_effect - expected_effect
  - expected_effect = effect1 + effect2 - (effect1 * effect2)
  - observed_effect predicted from embedding complementarity
  - synergy_score > 0 = synergistic
  - synergy_score ≈ 0 = additive
  - synergy_score < 0 = antagonistic
"""
